commit.message:
Merge pull request #30 from fxn/patch-1

Remove reference to examples directory in README

Remove reference to examples directory in README

The current README refers to the _examples_ directory for usage example, but this pointer is useless because the only file there has this code:

```ruby
code = File.read("README.md")[%r{<!-- example -->(.*)<!-- example -->}m].split("\n")[2..-3].join("\n")
puts code
eval code
```

1. This is not readable.
2. Obviously, there are no more examples than the ones already present in the README.
Release v0.4.0
Pin version of cucumber and drop 1.9.3 support
Add Ruby 2.3.1 to Travis

Avoid warnings

See grosser/maxitest/pull/16
Turn on warnings during tests
Release v0.3.2
Drop duplicate dependency on minitest

Drop global var to fix test dependency

Before this change tests might fail randomly due to their execute order.

This patch drop the usage of a global variable (which is evil anyway).

Fixes #29
Output the actual output on failed assertion
Workaround: MT emits an error while RSpec fails

Sync around_spec.feature from RSpec

See https://github.com/rspec/rspec-core/blob/1a08928ad98d1158d6a6f61108490addd71dacc3/features/hooks/around_hooks.feature

Drop rspec-expectations and convert `expect` manually

Because MT 5.6 introduced `expect` rspec-expectations stopped working.
Converting one (1) `expect` by hand seems easier.

Remove bump gem
Add code coverage via codeclimate

Fix badges refs in README
